| election_note      = January 12, 1898. Special election necessary because of the resignation of [[John Sherman (Ohio)|John Sherman]] to become [[United States Secretary of State]], March 4, 1897. Governor [[Asa S. Bushnell (Governor)|Asa Bushnell]] appointed Mark Hanna as senator, March 5, 1897, pending a meeting of the Ohio legislature. Hanna was elected on the first joint convention vote (73 votes needed for election). &quot;Short term&quot; election, to expire March 4, 1899.  See note to the long-term vote in next box for additional information as the votes on both elections were identical.
