{{compact election box
| election_title     = United States Senate election in [[Ohio]], 1904&lt;ref name = &quot;legislature 1904&quot;/&gt;
| election_note      = January 13, 1904. From March 4, 1905 for six years.  Each house met on January 12 and gave a majority of its vote to Hanna.  He was declared elected in joint convention following the reading of the journals; 71 votes needed for election. The breakdown was:  House, Hanna 86, Clarke 21; Senate, Hanna 29, Clarke 4.  Hanna died before this term commenced. [[Charles Dick]] was elected by the legislature on March 2, 1904 for the remainder of the term ending in 1905, and for the full term ending in 1911.
| result             = hold
